:Namespace GetTests

‚ćĚ Get req is the REST GET handler restricted to /files against
‚ćĚ AppState.RootFolder. The optional folder query parameter is resolved via
‚ćĚ ResolveSubfolder before CheckFolder classifies the result; CheckFolder and
‚ćĚ ResolveSubfolder outcomes map to HTTP status: 'not-found'->404,
‚ćĚ 'not-a-directory'->500 for the root itself or 404 for a requested
‚ćĚ subfolder, 'outside-root'->400. An unexpected failure while building the
‚ćĚ listing (permission denied, or the folder removed after Get resolved it)
‚ćĚ is a 500 rather than a stack trace. Unknown endpoints are a 404; the
‚ćĚ raw byte-serving /file endpoint is added in a later issue. req is
‚ćĚ whatever Jarvis's REST dispatcher passes: a stub exposing .Endpoint,
‚ćĚ .QueryParams, and a .Fail that records the status onto .Response.Status
‚ćĚ is enough, since Get touches nothing else on req.

    ‚ąá req‚Üźendpoint StubReqWithQuery params
      req‚Üź‚éēNS''
      req.Endpoint‚Üźendpoint
      req.QueryParams‚Üźparams
      req.Response‚Üź‚éēNS''
      req.Response.Status‚Üź200
      req.Fail‚Üź{Response.Status‚Üź‚ćĶ ‚čĄ ‚ćĶ}
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá req‚ÜźStubReq endpoint
      req‚Üźendpoint StubReqWithQuery(0 2‚ćī‚äā'')
    ‚ąá

    ‚ąá req‚Üźendpoint StubReqFolder folder;params
    ‚ćĚ Built with indexed assignment, not a struck-together literal: stranding
    ‚ćĚ two already-enclosed scalars encloses each one again, one level deeper
    ‚ćĚ than the cells of a real Jarvis QueryParams matrix (confirmed
    ‚ćĚ empirically against Jarvis.Request itself), which would make Get's own
    ‚ćĚ (unstranded) enclose-and-search lookup fail to match.
      params‚Üź1 2‚ćī‚äā''
      params[1;1]‚Üź‚äā'folder'
      params[1;2]‚Üź‚äāfolder
      req‚Üźendpoint StubReqWithQuery params
    ‚ąá

